Subject: Re: [VB] Turn signal switch

Take the turn signal switch off the steering column, and put a small piece
of rubber between it and the column.  Then put the switch back on and
tighten.  It shouldn't go anywhere after that.  Good luck.

Andrew
67 Deluxe Bus
75 914 1.8 (for sale)


